org.apache.ignite.ml.composition.stacking

Class StackedModel<IS,IA,O,AM extends IgniteModel<IA,O>>

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.apache.ignite.ml.composition.stacking.StackedModel<IS,IA,O,AM>
  • Type Parameters:
    IS - Type of submodels input.
    IA - Type of submodels output (same as aggregator model input).
    O - Type of aggregator model output.
    AM - Type of aggregator model.
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, AutoCloseable, IgniteModel<IS,O>, Model<IS,O>

    public final class StackedModel<IS,IA,O,AM extends IgniteModel<IA,O>>
extends Object
implements IgniteModel<IS,O>
    This is a wrapper for model produced by StackedDatasetTrainer. Model consisting of two layers: 
         1. Submodels layer  (IS -> IA).
     2. Aggregator layer  (IA -> O).
    Submodels layer is a ModelsParallelComposition of several models IS -> IA each of them getting same input IS and produce own output, these outputs outputs [IA] are combined into a single output with a given binary "merger" operator IA -> IA -> IA. Result of merge is then passed to the aggregator layer. Aggregator layer consists of a model IA -> O.
